==English==

===Etymology===
From {{der|en|enm|Messyas}}, {{m|enm|Messy}}, {{m|enm|Messie}}, from {{der|en|la|Messias}}, from Hellenistic {{der|en|grc|Μεσσίας}}, from {{der|en|arc|משיחא|tr=məšīḥā}}, from {{der|en|hbo|מָשִׁיחַ||anointed|tr=māšîaḥ}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{enPR|mə-sī'ə}}, {{IPA|/məˈsaɪ.ə/|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{lb|en|Abrahamic tradition}} The one who is ordained by [[God]] to lead the people of [[Israel]], believed by Christians and Muslims to be [[Jesus Christ]].
# {{lb|en|religion|loosely}} A similar religious figure or awaited divine ruler, such as the Islamic [[Mahdi]].
# {{lb|en|figuratively}} An extremely powerful figure.

